    <div style="color:black;font-family:arial,sans serif; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal;">
        <strong>Job Code:</strong> #13088<br/>
        <strong>Title:</strong> Analytic Data Scientist<br/>
        
        
        
        
            <strong>Job Type:</strong> Contract<br/>
        
        
        
            <strong>Job Location:</strong> 
            
            
                New York
             
                
            
                New York
            
            <br/>
        
        <br/>
        
    
            <strong>Job Description:</strong><br/>
            <br/>
            
                
            
            <p>Seeking a <b>Data Scientist for a part time consulting assignment for 3-4 months</b> with our <b>direct financial client in NYC, Ny</b>.&nbsp; For immediate consideration, please apply with a copy of your updated resume in <b>MS Word format</b> in order to proceed further.</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><b><font color="#FF0000">This is a part time role; 1-2 days per week for 3-6 months.</font></b></p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><b>Role:</b></p>

<p>Looking for a quantitative, motivated and entrepreneurial individual to design and implement a behavioral analytics project. The behavioral analytics project is about measuring skill and opportunity for portfolio managers to enhance alpha capture. The project is directly sponsored from the Chief Investment Officer and members of senior management.</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><b>Responsibilities:</b></p>

<ul>
	<li>Formulate portfolio optimization algorithms, ranging from constrained equal weight optimization to Black-Litterman optimization</li>
	<li>Mining trading and market data for behavioral patterns using data science techniques</li>
	<li>Contribute to implementing data analysis platform in Python pandas</li>
	<li>Contribute to visualizing results in reports and/or Tableau</li>
	<li>Work closely with members of the project team but also collaborate across the platform with investment, portfolio analytics, and risk teams.</li>
</ul>

<p>This is an excellent opportunity for somebody with a solid background in data science techniques and quantitative financial methods as well as a passion for financial markets to work on an innovative project that directly influences investment decisions.</p>

<p><b>Skills Required:</b></p>

<ul>
	<li><font color="#FF0000"><b>3+ years work experience in a relevant field is required </b></font></li>
	<li>Solid grasp of linear and non-linear optimization routines</li>
	<li>A good sense of the practical aspects of implementing optimization routines</li>
	<li>Intermediate understanding of machine learning techniques in both theory and practice. Advanced skills a big plus</li>
	<li><font color="#FF0000"><b>Excellent coding skills relevant for large-scale data analysis, ideally python (pandas/scipy), R, Matlab, SQL. Distributed computing in Hadoop, Spark etc a plus as is experience in ML libraries like scikit learn, TensorFlow</b></font></li>
	<li>Resourceful in translating theory/academic research into practical applications</li>
	<li>Ability to convincingly communicate your approach and results to a non-technical audience</li>
	<li>Entrepreneurial aptitude with the ability to turn unstructured tasks into actionable business results and proactively drive the design and implementation of the project</li>
</ul>

<p><b>Education:</b></p>

<ul>
	<li>Graduate or advanced degree in a relevant quantitative discipline.</li>
</ul>

<p>&nbsp;</p>
